[{"id":31569,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["Hexagonal","Orthorhombic","Monoclinic","Triclinic"],"answer":2,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mo>&#8800;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mo>&#8800;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#947;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>90</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>&#8800;</mo><mi>&#946;</mi></math>&nbsp;are parameters of monoclinic unit cell.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31562,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></math>forms ccp structure that means number of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>&nbsp;atoms per unit cell&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8594;</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>&nbsp;atoms per unit cell&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8594;</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;(Octahedral voids), as number of octahedral voids will be equal to number of atoms per unit cell.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>&nbsp;removed&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>&nbsp;left&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p><p>Formula becomes&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31600,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["Metal deficiency defect","Schottky defect","Vacancy defect","Frenkel defect"],"answer":3,"solution":"In Frenkel defect, some of the ions (usually cation due to their small size) missing from their correct position and occupies interstitial position.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (08 Apr)","image":null},{"id":31588,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["<math><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></math>","<math><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></msqrt></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;symmetrical cube<br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/78e8318c-5f93-454f-8b38-f9c6d87eec7b-image25.png\" /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5b656f1c-b9b8-4ba7-a0ef-8f526219ebf8-image26.png\" /><br />Distance between two <math><mtext>TV</mtext><mo>=</mo><mtext>a</mtext><mo>-</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mtext>a</mtext></mrow><mrow><mtext>4</mtext></mrow></mfrac><mtext>+</mtext><mfrac><mrow><mtext>a</mtext></mrow><mrow><mtext>4</mtext></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><br />Correct option is <math><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow></mfenced></math> .","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31607,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["<math> <mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>r</mtext> <msup> <mtext>Cs</mtext> <mo>+</mo> </msup> </msub> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <msub> <mtext>r</mtext> <msup> <mtext>Cl</mtext> <mo>-</mo> </msup> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <mn>3</mn> <mtext>a</mtext> </mrow> </math>","<math> <mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>r</mtext> <msup> <mtext>Cs</mtext> <mo>+</mo> </msup> </msub> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <msub> <mtext>r</mtext> <msup> <mtext>Cl</mtext> <mo>-</mo> </msup> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>3</mn> <mtext>a</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </math>","<math> <mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>r</mtext> <msup> <mtext>Cs</mtext> <mo>+</mo> </msup> </msub> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <msub> <mtext>r</mtext> <msup> <mtext>Cl</mtext> <mo>-</mo> </msup> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <msqrt> <mn>3</mn> </msqrt> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>a</mo> </mrow> </math>","<math> <mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>r</mtext> <msup> <mtext>Cs</mtext> <mo>+</mo> </msup> </msub> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <msub> <mtext>r</mtext> <msup> <mtext>Cl</mtext> <mo>-</mo> </msup> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <msqrt> <mn>3</mn> </msqrt> <mtext>a</mtext> </mrow> </math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<math> <mtext>8</mtext> </math> chloride ions at <math> <mtext>8</mtext> </math> corners <math> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mtext>Cs</mtext></mrow> <mtext>+</mtext> </msup> </mrow> </math> cation at body centre along body diagonal there will be one <math> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mtext>Cs</mtext></mrow> <mtext>+</mtext> </msup> </mrow> </math> cation and <math> <mrow> <mtext>2</mtext><mtext>&#8196;</mtext><msup> <mrow> <mtext>Cl</mtext></mrow> <mo>&#8722;</mo> </msup> </mrow> </math> ions at ends of body diagonal.<br /><math> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <msub> <mtext>r</mtext> <msup> <mtext>Cs</mtext> <mo>+</mo> </msup> </msub> <mo>+</mo> <mn>2</mn> <msub> <mtext>r</mtext> <msup> <mtext>Cl</mtext> <mo>-</mo> </msup> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <msqrt> <mn>3</mn> </msqrt> <mo>a</mo> </mrow> </math><br /><math> <mtext>a</mtext> </math> is edge length<br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9bd5c5b8-0e91-499e-be2f-eefe7ff2fb6e-image.png\" style=\"width: 160px; height: 191px;\" /><br />&nbsp;","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (06 Apr)","image":null},{"id":31582,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"/>In the ccp latice of oxide ions effective number of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi>ions</mi></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p><p>In the ccp latice,</p><p>No. of octahedral voids&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p><p>No. of tetrahedrla voids&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math></p><p>Given&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;atoms occupies&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn><mo>%</mo></math>&nbsp;of octahedral voids and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;atoms occupies&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp;of tetrahederal voids</p><p>No. of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;metal atoms&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>50</mn><mn>100</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p><p>No. of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;metal atoms&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>.5</mo></mrow><mn>100</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo></math>&nbsp;Formula of the compound&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msub><mfenced><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msub><mfenced><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo></math>&nbsp;Oxidation states of metals&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;respectively are&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (06 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31551,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["B and C only","B only","A and B only","A only"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Applying the electrical neutrality principle in metal deficiency defect.</p><p>One&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;is missing then two&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;ions are converted into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;ion so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>05</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;ion are missing and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>05</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;ion are converted in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;ion so for each&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;ion total&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;ion&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>85</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>A</mtext><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;ion is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p><p>Hence, A satisfies the condition.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (01 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31595,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>105</mn></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>205</mn></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>422</mn></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>211</mn></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"Crystal structure is <math><mi>F</mi><mi>C</mi><mi>C,</mi></math> so number of atoms per unit cell <math><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>N</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math><br /><br />Edge length <math><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>.</mo><msup><mrow><mi>&#8491;</mi></mrow><mrow></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8 &#160;</mn></mrow></msup><mi>c</mi><msup><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><br />Density <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>ZM</mi><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>63</mn><mo>.5</mo></mrow><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>.03</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>23</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><msup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mi>gm</mi><mo>/</mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math><br /><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>63.5</mn></mrow><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>6.0</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>422</mn></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mo>/</mo><mrow><mi>c</mi><msup><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>422</mn></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31609,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{AB}_3$","$\\mathrm{AB}_4$","$\\mathrm{A}_2 \\mathrm{~B}_5$","$\\mathrm{AB}_2$"],"answer":1,"solution":"A form corner points and two atoms of A are missing from corner\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\therefore \\quad & \\text { Atoms at corner }(\\mathrm{A})=6 \\times \\frac{1}{8}=\\frac{3}{4} \\\\\n& \\text { Atoms at face centre }(\\mathrm{B})=6 \\times \\frac{1}{2}=3 \\\\\n\\therefore & \\mathrm{A}_{3 / 4} \\mathrm{~B}_3 \\text { i.e., } \\mathrm{AB}_4\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (23 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":31583,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>a</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mi>a</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>In FCC octahedral voids are present at the edge centers and body center.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bf66da33-04ef-4ca9-9b22-754f8efdff3b-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 280px;\" /></p><p>Minimum distance between centers of two octahedral voids</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (05 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31615,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["tetrahedral","trigonal","octahedral","pyramidal"],"answer":2,"solution":"As per formula,\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\text { radius ratio } & =\\frac{\\text { radius of cation }}{\\text { radius of anion }} \\\\\n& =\\frac{94}{146}=0.643\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nSince the value is between $0.414-0.732$ hence the coordination no. will be 6 and geometry will be octahedral.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (12 May Online)","image":null},{"id":31564,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Number of effective atoms in HCP lattice is =6</p><p>Number of atoms of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn></math></p><p>Number of T.V. in h.c.p. =<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>Number</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>of</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>atoms</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Number of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math>&nbsp;atoms&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;atoms.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>%</mo></math>&nbsp;of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>14</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>42</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>86</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p><p>Round off to the nearest integer = 43</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (24 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31617,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["$314.20 \\mathrm{pm}$","$1.41 \\mathrm{pm}$","$200 \\mathrm{pm}$","$216 \\mathrm{pm}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"For bcc structure\n$$\nd=\\frac{\\sqrt{3} a}{2}\n$$\nwhere $d=$ distance between two atoms $a=$ edge length\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& 1.73=\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} a \\\\\n& a=\\frac{2 \\times 1.73}{\\sqrt{3}}=2 Å=200 \\mathrm{pm}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (07 May Online)","image":null},{"id":31605,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["Schottky defect","Frenkel defect","Interstitial position","F-centres"],"answer":3,"solution":"The appearance of colour in alkali metal halides is generally due to F-centres. F centers in $\\mathrm{NaCl}$ produce a band of optical absorption towards the blue end of visible\nspectrum, thus the colour appears yellow under transmitted light. On the other hand, $\\mathrm{KCl}$ with $\\mathrm{F}$-centers appears magenta, and $\\mathrm{KBr}$ appears blue.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (11 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":31599,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/wqohdttvwxelulvpplrnivkpizxhkzpqnmerqjgdgujgzlbenf.jpeg\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 37px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/lvezhjwffqjlnzwvbwofmbsnespvekpcihgxrxumrrdqqwiilt.jpeg\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 35px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/nfpgnmrapepobdvkmqhwgpmxoawvykffyhofmflrvaxoiganxe.jpeg\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 39px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/qeapbnrexxznxbiprgrbfnznymqxrnjqjmqpupgrnhwptvstca.jpeg\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 40px;\" />"],"answer":3,"solution":"Substances which are expected to possess para-magnetic or ferromagnetism on the basis of unpaired electrons, but actually they possess zero net magnetic moment are called anti-ferromagnetic substance.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr)","image":null},{"id":31587,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solid State","question":"","options":["<math><mn>4</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>4</mn></math>","<math><mn>4</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>3</mn></math>","<math><mn>8</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>6</mn></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mi>SC</mi></msub><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo></math></p><p>[Atoms are only at the corners]</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mi>BCC</mi></msub><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;</p><p>[Atoms are at the corners and at the body center]</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mi>FCC</mi></msub><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>[Atoms are at the corners and at the face centers]</p><p>Here,&nbsp;Z=&nbsp;effective number of atoms in the unit cell.</p><p>Therefore,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mi>SC</mi></msub><mo>&#8203;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mi>BCC</mi></msub><mo>&#8203;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mi>FCC</mi></msub><mo>&#8203;</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/355fb20b-1fd9-4fda-a088-cbe666e07245-image15.png\" /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/374cb6e0-20e0-4cf2-8131-dab7a3574466-image16.png\" /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/16c8d674-da79-4a5c-b202-6707fa0b21ca-image17.png\" /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>SC</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>BCC</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>FCC</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Apr Shift 2)","image":null}]